<br>
1) Shadowblades will always swing with both weapons<br>
<br>
2) Infiltrators will have more specialization points to take up Envenom<br>
<br>
When looking at Realm Abilities, Nightshades have some unique potential. But it is not free and comes at a cost where SB/Inf can spend their points elsewhere. Instead of analying it from the perspective that it increases your Envenom damage, I calculate things purely as a damage add, regardless of the source. On a per point basic, investing in Wild Arcana is not as beneficial as MoP, DR, or Dodger, but it does increase some damage overall. I didn't have much success with my Viper/WAIII Nightshade. I can see situations in hit and runs where chance strikes lucky in your favor and you make off with a critical can be beneficial in things like keep defense. When it comes to overall damage, your weapon damage will always be a higher percentage of your overall combat damage, more than poison. It is easier to see why MoP will add more damage since it focuses on the melee aspect of damage which occupies a larger portion of combat. If you do not stick around for combat, WAIII/Viper may work in your favor, but I found it mostly to get purged anyway and the target I went after was going to die anyway, Viper was only the final blow.<br>
<br>
In other words, for the same points that it takes a Nightshade to obtain WAIII, a SB/Inf gets more damage with MoPIII than a Nightshade with WAIII. The moment you start to say Nightshades are better at Envenom, you must equally say that SB/Infs will be better at Criticals or Dual Weapons. There is a tradeoff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrandynaquilius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brandyn Aquilius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/23/02 5:53:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3786.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightshades</span><hr size=1> Good points Elaa.  Although an infiltrator has more spec points, neither the Inf nor the NS will likely take their envenom past 39.  Granted, this is a choice each must make, but since this is the standard, I like to use it as a constant.<br>
<br>
WA affects envenom, but also affects the DDs I believe.  In every encounter I've had with NSs the DDs do get used, so there is another potential strength.<br>
<br>
NSs also have access to MoP and Dodger, so I think in the long run with all of these abilities, perhaps the NS is a bit ahead in envenom.  Additionaly, with a DW of 18 I seldom have to go past my Creeping Death to apply two poisons, and feel that the SB swinging with two weapons is not much of a balance in this area.<br>
<br>
Also, the Thrust Inf needs to take thrust to 50 to get Dragonfang (and I think most probably do); I wanted to keep my Thrust at 39, but that gave me little chance in 1v1s. A NS can be content at a lower number (39 maybe?).  This difference sucks up 445 spec points which is almost all of the difference between 2.2 and 2.5.  I'm not sure what slashers do, but since Diamond Slash has such great damage, I imagine many slashers to that route. <br>
<br>
Of course, having a higher weapon skill will mean more damage for those infiltrators. So the Inf should be ahead in pure melee damage.<br>
<br>
Infiltrators have been somewhat forced into being a melee class with envenom.  This is pretty much true all the way through the Infs career.  Would it be fair to say that early in his career, a shade is a melee class with a little envenom and a couple of spells, then later becomes an envenom class with decent melee and a couple of spells?  And have the NS spell variances been fixed yet?<br>
 <p>-Aurra Sing-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukreigmeister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreigmeister</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/23/02 7:39:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3786.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightshades</span><hr size=1> Well I have a spec similiar to Grollo's but i have made some mistakes with RA's. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I've also seen Grollo work and his template does work really well. Anyways here is my setup:<br>
